Bridgewater Companies

















Where innovation lives.






Home

Our Brands

Bridgepoint Systems
CRW Supply
Groom Industries Inc
Hydro-Force
Interlink Supply
OmniPro
Remote Field Commander
TES - Thermal Energy System
Water Claw

Contact Us










Bridgewater started as a privately held company founded in 1974 by three brothers; Rob, Gordon and Dave Hanks. From our humble roots as a local carpet cleaning business, we have since grown to a nationwide provider of a broad array of value-added manufacturing, marketing, distribution and financing services to the professional cleaning and restoration industries. A strong focus on innovation, customer service and quality has helped fuel our 30+ year track record of growth and success.
In 2014, Bridgewater was acquired by Aramsco, a New Jersey based company specializing in the distribution of products to the abatement, safety and restoration markets.
Manufacturing & Marketing
Bridgewater is a leading manufacturer and marketer of chemicals and equipment. We have more than 12,000 square feet dedicated to manufacturing activities, including a custom-designed building for chemical formulation bottling.
Distribution Services
Bridgewater/Aramsco offers the industry's broadest retail and wholesale selection with more than 5,000 items stocked and over 40 stores located across the US. We annually ship more than 3 million items from our national warehouses located in Salt Lake City, Utah and Nashville, Tennessee. Our direct-to-consumer shipment and fulfillment options offer unparalleled value to our customers and partners.
Markets Served
We serve contractors engaged in asbestos and lead abatement; fire, water and mold restoration; and surface preparation; as well as state and local government agencies, utilities, pharmaceuticals, hazardous material handlers, hospitals and facilities maintenance departments. We provide our customers with the sale of equipment and supplies, equipment repair and rental, education and training, technical support and same or next-day job site delivery.
About Aramsco
Aramsco, Inc., was founded as a regional supplier of industrial safety products in the 1960�s. For almost 50 years, the company evolved into a highly specialized distributor of safety products serving a diverse customer base. In February 2007, the company was merged with Bullseye Environmental, another leading environmental safety supplier, and Safeguard Industrial was formed.
Early in 2013, Aramsco was acquired by AEA Investors, through its Small Business Fund II. This partnership with AEA allowed Aramsco to further build its business organically and through acquisitions; the first of which was Crown Cleaning Supplies and Equipment, headquartered in Orlando, Florida. In August of 2014, Aramsco formed another partnership, this time with Bridgewater Companies (aka Interlink Supply and Aztec Financial).




©2017 Bridgewater, Inc.









